OL,3,CThe school using sensors and metal
OL,4,Cdetectors to protect their pupils from
OL,5,Cvapes
OL,7,F"The very first day that they were
OL,8,Ffitted they went off 112 times which
OL,9,Ftells us that some young people could
OL,10,Fnot last an hour without needing to
OL,11,Fcome and use the toilets so they could
OL,12,Fuse a vape."
OL,14,FThe sensors can detect vaping,
OL,15,Fcannabis and traditional smoking.
OL,17,FIt enables schools to monitor and act
OL,18,Fin real-time, identifying problem
OL,19,Flocations, reducing classroom
OL,20,Fdisruption and aiming to improve
OL,21,Fstudents' health.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
