OL,3,CThe school using sensors and metal
OL,4,Cdetectors to protect their pupils from
OL,5,Cvapes
OL,7,FAs well as the obvious dangers of
OL,8,Fillegal vapes police say predators are
OL,9,Fnow using vapes to sexually and
OL,10,Fcriminally exploit children.
OL,12,FDetective Chief Inspector Thompson
OL,13,Fadded: "We have seen situations where
OL,14,Fby children are sold or given vapes
OL,15,Ffor free - that might happen once or
OL,16,Ftwice and then after that point they
OL,17,Fare told they owe money and then that
OL,18,Fchild can become debt bonded to an
OL,19,Fexploiter and be told that they have
OL,20,Fto do things.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
